ical models\nthat best reproduce the observations. We obtain an independent constraint of\n4.8 +/- 0.5 km for the aerosol scale height in the upper haze region above 80\nkm. We show that a full multiple-layer approach is required to adequately\nreproduce the aureole photometry, which appears to be sensitive to several\nsecond-order variations in the vertical refractivity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Aug 2016 16:27:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-09"}
