s. We therefore suggest that\nthe relation between the environment and GC colors is, at least in part, due to\nchemical abundance variations, which affect stellar spectra and stellar\nevolution tracks. Our results demonstrate that stellar population diagnostics\nderived from model predictions which are calibrated on one particular sample of\nGCs may not be appropriate for all extragalactic GCs. These results advocate a\nmore complex model of the assembly history of GC systems in massive galaxies\nthat goes beyond the simple bimodality found in previous decades.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 30 Aug 2016 20:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-21"}
