eries photometry\nshows a periodicity of $P=5.743$ d, which is also seen in SOPHIE spectra as an\nRV modulation of the star A. We interpret it as being caused by spots on the\nstellar surface, and the star to be rotating with the given period. From the\nrotation and level of activity, we found that the system is $380^{+220}_{-100}$\nMyr old, consistent with an isochrone analysis ($220^{+2120}_{-90}$ Myr). This\nwork may serve as a test case for future studies of low-mass stars, brown\ndwarfs and exoplanets by combination of RV and direct imaging data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 31 Aug 2016 01:48:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-23"}
