ove 100 K - we attribute this to warm gas associated with the\nother massive dense cores in W43 MM1. Using the maps to identify absorption\nfrom cool gas on large scales, we subtract this component to model spectra for\nthe inner envelope. Modeling the new spectra results in a lower water\nabundance, decreased from $8 10^{-8}$ to $8 10^{-9}$ , with no change in infall\nrate.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 31 Aug 2016 09:06:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-02"}
