 great detail. It\nis shown that the phenomenology is similar to the above case where the MSSM\nfields are inert, with the exception of the stop squark, which can be as light\nas $1.5$ TeV.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 31 Aug 2016 13:28:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-01"}
